Package software.leonov.common.collect

Class MoreArrays

  • java.lang.Object
    • software.leonov.common.collect.MoreArrays
  • public final class MoreArrays
extends Object
    Static utility methods which operate on or return arrays.

    This class is useful for working with legacy APIs. It holds an advantage over similar Java or Guava equivalents because its methods do not create intermediate objects. Still, it is often preferable to represent arrays as Lists, consider using Arrays.asList(Object[]) or Guava's ImmutableList.copyOf(Object[]).

    When not working with legacy APIs users should always prefer Collection types to arrays.

    Note: Methods in this class accept java.util.function.Predicates while their Guava counterparts accept com.google.common.base.Predicates, the two objects are interchangeable, see com.google.common.base.Predicate for more information.
